<paper id="1621441552"><title>A Supermodular Relaxation for Scheduling with Release Dates</title><year>1996</year><authors><author org="M. I. T" id="667657047">Michel X. Goemans</author></authors><n_citation>46</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>1498671329</reference><reference>1500197053</reference><reference>1680189815</reference><reference>1960330418</reference><reference>1968143987</reference><reference>2075265959</reference><reference>2085325317</reference><reference>2159152246</reference></references><venue id="1184093072" type="C">Integer Programming and Combinatorial Optimization</venue><doi>10.1007/3-540-61310-2_22</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.45923">Mathematical optimization</keyword><keyword weight="0.58099">Job shop scheduling</keyword><keyword weight="0.0">Release date</keyword><keyword weight="0.52266">Scheduling (computing)</keyword><keyword weight="0.43002">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.44628">Parallel computing</keyword><keyword weight="0.49077">Polyhedron</keyword><keyword weight="0.47972">Transportation theory</keyword><keyword weight="0.54283">Greedy algorithm</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>We consider the scheduling problem of minimizing a weighted sum of completion times under release dates. We present a relaxation which is a supermodular polyhedron. We show that this relaxation is precisely the projection of a time-indexed relaxation introduced by Dyer and Wolsey.</abstract></paper>